doc.previous: In August 2014, Jet Airways announced that it is discontinuing its low fare arm JetKonnect and JetLite making Jet Airways 3rd full service airline in India besides Air India and Vistara.
doc.after: Jet Airways's head office is located in the Siroya Centre in Andheri, Mumbai.[30] Jet Airways's head office was previously located in the S.M. Centre, a rented, unmarked six-storey building in Andheri.[31][32] In 2008 Robyn Meredith of Forbes stated that the complex was "as shabby as [Jet Airways] CEO Naresh Goyal's home is posh" and that the complex was "In need of a fresh coat of paint". The complex was 15 minutes driving time from Chhatrapati Shivaji International Airport.[32] In 2013, it was announced that Etihad Airways would buy a 24% stake in the airline through preferential allotment of shares.[33]
